OL,5,CA&E
OL,7,FThe research also found that the
OL,8,Flikelihood of experiencing a 12-hour
OL,9,Fwait in an emergency department
OL,10,Fincreases with the age of the patient.
OL,12,FPeople aged 60-69 have a 15% chance of
OL,13,Fwaiting 12 hours or more, whereas for
OL,14,Fthose aged 90 and above, the
OL,15,Flikelihood rises to 33%.
OL,17,FThe RCEM has been looking in detail at
OL,18,Fthe care older people receive and also
OL,19,Ffound that many are missing out on
OL,20,Fvital checks in A&E.
