OL,7,F` Only 16% of patients were screened
OL,8,Ffor delirium ` a reversible condition
OL,9,Fwhich is linked to increase risk of
OL,10,Fdeath and is noted by a sudden change
OL,11,Fin mental function.
OL,13,F` On average, fewer than half (48%) of
OL,14,Fpatients were screened for their risk
OL,15,Fof falls.
OL,17,F` Just over half (56%) were screening
OL,18,Ffor general frailty ` which if picked
OL,19,Fup early can lead to prompt extra
OL,20,Fsupport in hospital and at home.
